USE CASE: Population report for all districts
CHARACTERISTIC INFORMATION
Goal in Context

As a researcher, I want to view the population of all districts, so that I can understand the distribution of population across districts.

Scope

Population Reporting System

Level

Primary task

Preconditions

The SQL database is connected.

The database contains valid population data for all districts and their cities.

Success End Condition

A report is displayed showing all districts with:

District Name

Country

Total population of the district (sum of all cities in that district)

Failed End Condition

No report is produced, and the system displays an appropriate message.

Primary Actor

Data researcher

Trigger

The researcher runs the method for “Population report for all districts.”

MAIN SUCCESS SCENARIO

The researcher runs the method “Population report for all districts.”

The system checks the database connection.

The system constructs an SQL query to retrieve all districts and calculate the total population of each district.

The system executes the SQL query.

The system sorts the result by total district population in descending order.

The system formats the output with columns: District Name, Country, and Population.

The report is successfully generated.

EXTENSIONS

Database connection error: Display “Database unavailable” and log the issue.

SQL execution error: Query failed and display an error message.

No matching data found: Display “No data found.” and return to the main menu.

SUB-VARIATIONS

Optionally, allow filtering districts by country or region.

SCHEDULE

DUE DATE: date or release of deployment
